<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,476,151,177]" pageId="2" pageNumber="42">
<taxonomicName box="[151,315,151,177]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Oedematopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,315,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="42">Oedematopus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
genus group
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,222,462]" pageId="2" pageNumber="42">
The 
<taxonomicName box="[202,356,222,246]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Oedematopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[202,356,222,246]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="42">Oedematopus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
genus group appears to be a monophyletic clade within the 
<taxonomicName box="[1032,1204,222,246]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Hydrophorinae">Hydrophorinae</taxonomicName>
, but it is still premature to establish a new tribe. The group can be separated by the following combination of characters: arista dorsal; vertical setae absent; palpus narrow and pointed apically; mesonotum with silvery white pruinosity; acrostichal setae absent; 
<number box="[300,314,330,354]" pageId="2" pageNumber="42" value="6.0">6</number>
dorsocentrals; 
<number box="[485,499,330,354]" pageId="2" pageNumber="42" value="2.0">2</number>
scutellars; crossvein dm-cu parallel or at acute angle to posterior wing margin; fore tarsomeres in males sometimes modified (
<collectionCode box="[620,701,366,390]" pageId="2" pageNumber="42">MSSC</collectionCode>
); hind coxa without strong lateral seta; mid and hind femora without preapical seta; pulvilli absent; usually two pairs of epandrial lobes; surstylus divided into dorsal and ventral lobe; postgonite present.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
